text: Mount Manipur National Park, formerly Mount Harriet National Park, is a national park in Andaman and Nicobar Islands of India. The park contains Mount Manipur (formerly, Mount Harriet), the third highest mountain in the entire archipelago with a height of 383 metres. ==Related page== * Mount Manipur (Mount Harriet) ==References== Category:National parks in India
title: Mount Manipur National Park
